{"comments":"GlyphGeometry — Typography as pure geometry.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nA glyph is NOT special-cased text rendering. A glyph IS a shape: bezier\npaths that can be manipulated, extruded, beveled, and animated like any\nother vector geometry. The letter 'O' is two elliptical paths (outer and\ncounter). The letter 'A' is three line segments. This unifies the entire\nrendering pipeline.\n\n## Structure\n\n- GlyphPath: Complete character with metadata (advance width, bounds)\n- Contour: Single closed path within a glyph (glyphs may have multiple)\n- ContourWinding: Clockwise (outer) or counter-clockwise (hole)\n- ControlPoint3D: Point in 3D space for per-control-point animation\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude (Eq, Ord, Show)\n- Schema.Dimension.Device (Pixel for coordinates)\n- Schema.Geometry.Shape (PathCommand for path operations)\n- Schema.Bounded (clamping utilities)\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"A single character rendered as bezier geometry.\n\nThis is the fundamental unit of typography-as-geometry. A GlyphPath\ncontains all bezier paths needed to render a single character, including\nouter boundaries and counter-shapes (holes).\n\n## Structure\n\n- contours: Array of closed paths. First is usually outer, rest are counters.\n- bounds: Pre-computed 3D bounding box for layout and culling.\n- advanceWidth: Horizontal distance to next glyph origin.\n- leftSideBearing: Space before the glyph's visible bounds.\n\n## Animation\n\nEach control point can be individually animated via `mapControlPoints`.\nThe structure preserves contour and command indices for targeting.\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["contours",{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","GlyphGeometry"],"Contour"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["bounds",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","GlyphGeometry"],"GlyphBounds"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["advanceWidth",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Device","Types"],"Pixel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["leftSideBearing",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Device","Types"],"Pixel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[345,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/GlyphGeometry.purs","start":[340,1]},"title":"GlyphPath"},{"children":[],"comments":"A single closed contour (subpath) of a glyph.\n\nEvery glyph consists of one or more contours:\n- Simple letters ('l', 'v', 'z'): 1 contour\n- Letters with holes ('o', 'a', 'e'): 2+ contours\n- Complex letters ('8', 'B', '&'): multiple contours\n\nEach contour MUST be closed. The winding direction determines\nwhether it contributes to fill (outer) or removes from fill (hole).\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["commands",{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","GlyphGeometry"],"PathCommand3D"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["winding",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","GlyphGeometry"],"ContourWinding"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[208,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/GlyphGeometry.purs","start":[205,1]},"title":"Contour"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[186,21],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/GlyphGeometry.purs","start":[186,3]},"title":"WindingClockwise"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[187,28],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/GlyphGeometry.purs","start":[187,3]},"title":"WindingCounterClockwise"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","GlyphGeometry"],"ContourWinding"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[189,54],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/GlyphGeometry.purs","start":[189,1]},"title":"eqContourWinding"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","GlyphGeometry"],"ContourWinding"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[190,56],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/GlyphGeometry.purs","start":[190,1]},"title":"ordContourWinding"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","GlyphGeometry"],"ContourWinding"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[194,39],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/GlyphGeometry.purs","start":[192,1]},"title":"showContourWinding"}],"comments":"Winding direction of a contour.\n\nDetermines fill behavior using the non-zero winding rule:\n- WindingClockwise: Outer boundary (adds to fill)\n- WindingCounterClockwise: Hole/counter (subtracts from fill)\n\nFor glyphs like 'O', 'A', 'B', '8':\n- The outer shape is clockwise\n- The inner hole(s) are counter-clockwise\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[187,28],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/GlyphGeometry.purs","start":[185,1]},"title":"ContourWinding"},{"children":[],"comments":"A control point in 3D space.\n\nThe Z coordinate enables:\n- Depth-based stacking for overlapping paths\n- 3D transformations for perspective typography\n- Animation along the Z axis (letters floating up)\n- Extrusion reference points\n\nAll coordinates in Pixel units. Z is bounded to prevent extreme values\nat swarm scale: -10000 to 10000 pixels depth.\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["x",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Device","Types"],"Pixel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["y",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Device","Types"],"Pixel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["z",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Device","Types"],"Pixel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[119,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/GlyphGeometry.purs","start":[115,1]},"title":"ControlPoint3D"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create a 3D control point with Z clamping.\n\nZ coordinate clamped to -10000..10000 to ensure bounded depth.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Device","Types"],"Pixel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Device","Types"],"Pixel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Device","Types"],"Pixel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","GlyphGeometry"],"ControlPoint3D"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[124,60],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/GlyphGeometry.purs","start":[124,1]},"title":"controlPoint3D"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create a control point from 2D coordinates (Z = 0).\n\nStandard case for flat typography before extrusion.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Device","Types"],"Pixel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Device","Types"],"Pixel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","GlyphGeometry"],"ControlPoint3D"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[137,51],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/GlyphGeometry.purs","star